cs.MM, cs.HC, cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.CL 

This paper involves affect recognition from ads, which is a topic related to multimedia (cs.MM) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also uses convolutional neural networks (cs.CV) and electroencephalogram (EEG) signals (cs.IR) for analysis. Additionally, the paper involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques for analyzing subjective viewer experience (cs.CL).
